East 133rd Street, east from Cypress Ave. In the background is the United Electric Light and Power Co. plant on the East River Shore.

April 12, 1931.

P. L. Sperr.

108 to 88 Cypress Ave., at, adjoining and south of the S.E. corner of East 133rd Street. The 1-story brick structures are garages.

April 12, 1931.

P. L. Sperr.

114 to 120 Cypress Ave., adjoining and north of the N.E. corner of East 133rd Street. The corner was occupied by No. 112, another 3-story frame house.

April 12, 1931.

P. L. Sperr.

(1) 100-116 Southern Boulevard, at the S.W. corner of Cypress Ave., showing the Jacob Doll & Sons piano factory. The long side of the factory building extends south on Cypress Ave. to East 133rd Street. Southern Boulevard runs south from the extreme right, where automobile is seen, to the right background. On the left is East 134th Street.

P. L. Sperr.

September 26, 1934.

(2) The same, at a later date.

P. L. Sperr.

April 4, 1936.

(3) The same, an additional view. Also shown (left), at the S.E. corner of Cypress Ave., and East 134th Street is the factory of the Standard Musical String and Manufacturing Corporation, bearing No. 122 on the former.

P. L. Sperr.
